  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Quality of life after rectal surgery is reported to be impaired. Side effects of surgery
      and/or neoadjuvant treatment as functional disturbances like sexual dysfunction, urinary
      incontinence, anal incontinence or stoma problems are commonly experienced. The investigators
      hypotheses is that structured rehabilitation program addressing these problems will improve
      quality of life. A RCT are performed in order to document the effects of the rehabilitation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
